sub_title: Chemical biologist with a passion for X-ray crystallography.
summary:
Rasmus holds an MSc. in Chemistry as well as a BSc. in molecular biology; from Gothenburg University. He spent the last semester of the Master’s degree program on an Erasmus exchange program to the Norwegian University of Life Sciences in Ås, Norway.

Rasmus is currently located in Amsterdam working at the Vrije Universitet with protein expression, and purification. 

During the master’s degree project Rasmus crystalized purified membrane protein and tested the protein crystals at the Max IV beamline in Lund, Sweden. This project was presented at the 2019 SWEPROT/SBNet conference in Tällberg, Sweden. 

Rasmus developed, throughout the Bachelor’s- and Master’s degree projects a holistic experience in the laboratory environment. He is proficient with multiple molecular biology and biochemistry techniques and methods. 

During the pandemic, Rasmus completed his master’s degree and lead a group of three with the distribution of PPE and SARS-COV-2 antigen rapid diagnostic tests, to the municipals of southern Norway. Furthermore, Rasmus works part-time as an ice hockey official, currently working the highest league in the netherlands.  

Rasmus is a team player, and he enjoys challenges, efficiency and prospers in a fast-paced work environment. He’s agreeable and dedicated to his work. He works well under pressure and remains optimistic about solving the problem at hand.
